34static void
35gm20b_gr_init_gpc_mmu(struct gf100_gr *gr)
36{
37 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
38 u32 val;
39
40 /* TODO this needs to be removed once secure boot works */
41 if (1) {
42 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100ce4, 0xffffffff);
43 }
44
45 /* TODO update once secure boot works */
46 val = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100c80);
47 val &= 0xf000087f;
48 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x418880, val);
49 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x418890, 0);
50 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x418894, 0);
51
52 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4188b0, nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100cc4));
53 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4188b4, nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100cc8));
54 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4188b8, nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100ccc));
55
56 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4188ac, nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100800));
57}
